Tutu - A skimpy outfit for Dancer 

Tutu is a flat-file CMS inspired by Blosxom.  Pages are
created as textfiles, typically formatted with Markdown.
Tutu is based on the Dancer web framework.
 
Tutu is configured as a website to display pages and to
distribute media files for training course. It requires
login, authenticated users may upload and download files.

INSTALLATION

To install this module, you may run the following commands:

	perl Makefile.PL
	make
	make test
	make install

CUSTOMIZING THE DEFAULT WEBAPP TEMPLATE

	Edit MY_WEBSITE_INIT to suit your planned site.
	Run this script:

    ./customize.pl

	Test your app by starting the local webserver and
	pointing your browser to http://localhost:3000

	cd $WEBSITE_ROOT

	./dance.psgi

    Move the $WEBSITE_ROOT and $WEBSITE_DOMAIN directories
    to the appropriate locations, if desired.

